description: From Middle English upspringen, from Old English uppspringan, ūpspringan, equivalent to up- +‎ spring.

verbs.description: upspring (third-person singular simple present upsprings, present participle upspringing, simple past upsprang or upsprung, past participle upsprung)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To spring up, rise up, originate, come into being.
examples: In diamond light upspring the dazzling peaks Of Pyramids

description: From Middle English upspring, upspringe, from Old English upspring (“origin, birth, rising up, springing up”), equivalent to up- +‎ spring. Cognate with Old Saxon upspring (“well; source; spring”), Middle Low German upspringen (“to spring up; grow”).

entries.meaning: A spring or leap into the air.
